---
/**
 * Privacy Policy — socialWarmer.
 *
 * Structure mirrors the Mail Warmer privacy page, rewritten for socialWarmer:
 * a free extension with no account, no payments, and no backend at all.
 * Everything — settings, run state, logs, transcripts — lives in the
 * browser's local storage.
 */
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const lastUpdated = "Last updated: June 10, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — socialWarmer"
  description="Privacy Policy for the socialWarmer browser extension. Everything runs locally; nothing you browse leaves your computer."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="relative z-10 min-h-screen px-4 pt-32 pb-20 md:px-6">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
        Privacy <span class="legal-accent">Policy</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-stone-500">{lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6">
        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">1. The short version</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            socialWarmer is a free browser extension that warms social accounts
            by browsing the way you would. It has no account system, no
            backend, and no analytics. Everything it knows — your settings,
            run history, logs, saved videos, and transcripts — lives in your
            browser's local storage and never leaves your machine.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">2. What stays on your device</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            All of the following is stored locally in your browser, visible
            only to the extension:
          </p>
          <ul class="legal-ul">
            <li>Your run settings (platform, mode, keyword, target, persona, pacing, thresholds)</li>
            <li>Run state and the live activity log</li>
            <li>Videos your runs saved and their links</li>
            <li>Transcripts generated by the local speech-to-text model</li>
            <li>Thumbnails you download (saved straight to your Downloads folder)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="legal-p mt-3">None of this is sent to us or to anyone else.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">3. What touches the network</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            Only the platforms themselves. The extension interacts with
            Facebook, Instagram, and TikTok in your own logged-in browser
            session, exactly as your own clicks would. There is no
            socialWarmer server: no telemetry, no crash reporting, no usage
            analytics, no remote configuration. The one optional download is
            the local Whisper speech-to-text model, fetched once from a public
            model host and cached in your browser.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">4. Your platform credentials</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            socialWarmer never sees, asks for, or stores your passwords. It
            operates on pages you are already logged into, using your
            browser's existing session. Logging in — and staying logged in —
            is entirely between you and the platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">5. Local AI transcription</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            The Transcripts feature runs a Whisper speech-to-text model
            entirely inside your browser. Audio from videos you choose to
            transcribe is processed on your machine and the resulting text is
            stored locally. No audio or text is uploaded anywhere.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">6. Permissions, explained</h2>
          <ul class="legal-ul">
            <li><strong class="text-ink">Site access (Facebook / Instagram / TikTok)</strong> — needed to scroll, watch, and engage on those sites at your command.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-ink">Storage</strong> — keeps your settings and run state between sessions.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-ink">Side panel</strong> — hosts the control panel UI.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-ink">Downloads</strong> — saves reel thumbnails to your Downloads folder when you ask.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-ink">Tabs</strong> — finds the platform tab the panel should control.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">7. Cookies & tracking</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            The extension sets no cookies and embeds no trackers. This website
            is static and analytics-free.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">8. Children</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            socialWarmer is not directed at children under 13 and should only
            be used by people old enough to hold accounts on the platforms it
            supports.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-card">
          <h2 class="legal-h2">9. Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p class="legal-p">
            If the privacy model ever changes — for example, if an optional
            online feature is added — this page will be updated first, with
            the date above bumped, before any such feature ships.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="legal-link text-stone-500">← Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .legal-accent {
    color: var(--color-blue);
  }
  .legal-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(224, 227, 231, 0.8);
    background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    border-radius: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.6rem;
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
  }
  .legal-h2 {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-p {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal-ul {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    list-style: disc;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal-ul > li + li {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }
  .legal-link {
    color: var(--color-blue);
    background-image: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-blue), #59c0e8);
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: 0% 1.5px;
    background-position: 0 100%;
    transition:
      color 300ms ease,
      background-size 350ms cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1);
  }
  .legal-link:hover,
  .legal-link:focus-visible {
    background-size: 100% 1.5px;
    outline: none;
  }
</style>
